Ingredients

	* normal2 Tbsp olive oil $0.22
	* normal½ large red onion $0.65
	* normal2 inches fresh ginger $0.30
	* normal1 Tbsp minced garlic $0.24
	* normal½ Tbsp turmeric $0.07
	* normal½ tsp cumin $0.03
	* normal½ tsp cinnamon $0.03
	* normal¼ tsp crushed red pepper $0.02
	* normal1 whole bay leaf $0.15
	* normal2 lb. chicken (breast or thigh) $3.98
	* normal1 (15 oz.) can diced tomatoes $1.17
	* normal1 (13. oz.) can coconut milk $2.15
	* normalto taste salt & pepper $0.05
	* normal¼ bunch cilantro (optional) $0.20
	* normal2 cups uncooked jasmine rice $0.88

Instructions

	1. Combine the jasmine rice with 3 cups of cold water in a medium pot. Place a lid on top and bring up to a boil over high heat. As soon as it reaches a rolling boil, reduce the heat to low and let simmer for 30 minutes. After 30 minutes, turn the heat off and let it sit undisturbed until you are ready to serve it.
	2. Dice the onion, mince the garlic, and grate the ginger using a small cheese grater. Saute all three in a large pot over medium heat with 2 Tbsp. of olive oil.
	3. When the onions have softened, add the turmeric, cumin, cinnamon, and red pepper. Saute for 2 minutes. Dice the chicken and add to the pot. Saute until cooked through (7-10 minutes).
	4. Add the can of tomatoes and the bay leaf. Place a lid on top and let simmer for 30 minutes. Turn the heat off and stir in the coconut milk. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Fluff the rice with a fork. Serve the stewed chicken mixture over a heaping portion of rice. Sprinkle fresh cilantro on top if desired.

